16 (2) "Homestead" means homestead as defined and qualified in Code Section 48-5-40 of
17 the O.C.G.A., as amended, with the additional qualification that it shall include not more
18 than five contiguous acres of homestead property.
19 (3) "Senior citizen" means a person who is 65 years of age or older on or before January
20 1 of the year in which application for the exemption under subsection (b) of this section
21 is made.
22 (b) Each resident of the Jasper County school district who is a senior citizen is granted an
23 exemption on such person's homestead from Jasper County school district ad valorem taxes
24 for educational purposes in the amount of $40,000.00 of the assessed value of such
25 homestead. The value of that property in excess of such exempted amount shall remain
26 subject to taxation.
27 (c) A person shall not receive the homestead exemption granted by subsection (b) of this
28 section unless such person or person's agent files an application with the tax commissioner
29 of Jasper County, giving such person's age and such additional information relative to
30 receiving such exemption as will enable the tax commissioner of Jasper County to make a
31 determination regarding the initial and continuing eligibility of such person for such
32 exemption; provided, however, that any qualifying person who has already applied for and
33 been granted an exemption from Jasper County school district ad valorem taxes for
34 educational purposes granted by an Act to provide a homestead exemption from certain
35 Jasper County ad valorem taxes for county purposes in the amount of $2,000.00 of the
36 assessed value of that homestead for certain residents of that county, approved April 17, 1992
37 (Ga. L. 1992, p. 6508), as amended by an Act approved March 27, 1998 (Ga. L. 1998,
38 p. 3829), shall automatically qualify for and be granted the exemption provided for by
39 subsection (b) of this section without needing to reapply. The tax commissioner of Jasper
40 County shall provide application forms for this purpose.
41 (d) The exemption shall be claimed and returned as provided in Code Section 48-5-50.1 of
42 the O.C.G.A., as amended. The exemption shall be automatically renewed from year to year
