43 so long as the person granted the homestead exemption under subsection (b) of this section
44 occupies the residence as a homestead. After such person has filed the proper application as
45 provided in subsection (c) of this section, it shall not be necessary to make application
46 thereafter for any year, and such exemption shall continue to be allowed to such person. It
47 shall be the duty of any such person granted the homestead exemption under subsection (b)
48 of this section to notify the tax commissioner of Jasper County in the event that such person
49 for any reason becomes ineligible for such exemption. The surviving spouse of the person
50 who has been granted the exemption provided for in subsection (b) of this section shall
51 continue to receive the exemption provided under subsection (b) of this section, so long as
52 that surviving spouse continues to occupy the home as a residence and homestead.
53 (e) The exemption granted by subsection (b) of this section shall not apply to or affect any
54 state ad valorem taxes, county ad valorem taxes for county purposes, municipal ad valorem
55 taxes for municipal purposes, or independent school district ad valorem taxes for educational
56 purposes. The homestead exemption granted by subsection (b) of this section shall be in
57 addition to and not in lieu of any other homestead exemption applicable to Jasper County
58 school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes; provided, however, that this
59 exemption granted by subsection (b) of this section shall be in lieu of and not in addition to
60 any exemption granted by an Act to provide a homestead exemption from certain Jasper
61 County ad valorem taxes for county purposes in the amount of $2,000.00 of the assessed
62 value of that homestead for certain residents of that county, approved April 17, 1992 (Ga.
63 L. 1992, p. 6508), as amended by an Act approved March 27, 1998 (Ga. L. 1998, p. 3829).
64 (f) The exemption granted by subsection (b) of this section shall apply to all taxable years
65 beginning on or after January 1, 2026.
