66 SECTION 2.
67 In accordance with the requirements of Article VII, Section II of the Constitution of the State
68 of Georgia, this Act shall not become law unless it receives the requisite two-thirds' majority
69 vote in both the Senate and the House of Representatives.
70 SECTION 3.
71 The election superintendent of Jasper County shall call and conduct an election as provided
72 in this section for the purpose of submitting this Act to the electors of the Jasper County
73 school district for approval or rejection. The election superintendent shall conduct that
74 election on the Tuesday following the first Monday in November, 2025, and shall issue the
75 call and conduct that election as provided by general law. The election superintendent shall
76 cause the date and purpose of the election to be published once a week for two weeks
77 immediately preceding the date thereof in the official organ of Jasper County. The ballot
78 shall have written or printed thereon the words:
79 "( ) YES Shall the Act be approved which provides a homestead exemption from
80 Jasper County school district ad valorem taxes for educational purposes in
81 ( ) NO the amount of $40,000.00 of the assessed value of the homestead for
82 residents of that school district who are 65 years of age or older?"
83 All persons desiring to vote for approval of the Act shall vote "Yes," and all persons desiring
84 to vote for rejection of the Act shall vote "No." If more than one-half of the votes cast on
85 such question are for approval of the Act, Section 1 of this Act shall become of full force and
86 effect on January 1, 2026. If the Act is not so approved or if the election is not conducted
87 as provided in this section, Section 1 of this Act shall not become effective, and this Act shall
88 be automatically repealed on the 365th calendar day following the election date provided for
89 in this section. The expense of such election shall be borne by Jasper County. It shall be the
90 election superintendent's duty to certify the result thereof to the Secretary of State. The
91 provisions of this section shall be mandatory upon the election superintendent and are not
